Node.Notes: Some think a noun meaning "confession." Probably refers to Jeduthun, one of David's chief musicians (1c16:41). Also possible to be a musical tune/setting named after Jeduthun.
Apparently, something like "I refrain from speaking, even from [speaking] good."
Uncertain. Probably take "stand" in some sense as referring to life/enduring and so "each man's life is but a breadth."
Sense is to turn aside the face of anger and discipline so that I can live and die in peace.
